I then revisited the code and realized that even if the allocation succeeds (e.g., OOM killer intervenes), the warning *will* be emitted. However, if an allocation loops *indefinitely* and never reaches either `fail` or `got_pg`, it will *never* warn. This definitely warrants a report as a potential issue, as it defeats the diagnostic purpose of the warning.

